@startuml
!theme plain
skinparam componentStyle rectangle

' === Subsystems as Components ===
component "Prescription Management" as PM
component "Verification Subsystem" as VS
component "EventBus" as EB
component "Notification Subsystem" as NS
component "Analytics & Fraud Detection" as AF
component "Scheduling Subsystem" as SS
component "User Management & RBAC" as UM
component "Patient Services" as PS

database "Centralized Database" as DB

' === Interfaces ===
interface "IPrescriptionLifecycle" as I_PM
interface "IVerification" as I_VS
interface "IEventPublisher" as I_EB_Pub
interface "IEventSubscriber" as I_EB_Sub
interface "INotification" as I_NS
interface "IRBAC" as I_UM

' === Component Details (using notes instead of inline brackets) ===
note top of PM
  - PrescriptionBuilder
  - PrescriptionStateManager
  - State implementations
end note

note top of VS
  - Chain of Responsibility
  - Validation Handlers
end note

note top of EB
  <<centralized>>
  - publish()
  - subscribe()
  - Event persistence
end note

note top of NS
  - NotificationFacade
  - EmailStrategy
  - SMSStrategy
  - PushStrategy
end note

note top of AF
  - AnalyticsObserver
  - Pattern Detectors
  - Fraud Rules Engine
end note

note top of SS
  - SchedulerService
  - Cron jobs
  - Expiry Manager
end note

note top of UM
  - UserService
  - RoleRepository
  - AuthorizationFilter
end note

note top of PS
  - History Viewer
  - Schedule Tracker
  - Safety Info Provider
end note

note bottom of DB
  <<single source of truth>>
  - Prescriptions
  - Users
  - Audit Logs
end note

' === Interface Providers ===
PM ..> I_PM
VS ..> I_VS
EB ..> I_EB_Pub
EB ..> I_EB_Sub
NS ..> I_NS
UM ..> I_UM

' === Connections ===
VS --> PM : uses <<REST/gRPC>>
PM --> EB : publishes events to

NS ..> I_EB_Sub
AF ..> I_EB_Sub
SS ..> I_EB_Sub

PM --> DB : reads/writes
VS --> DB : reads
UM --> DB : reads/writes
PS --> DB : reads
AF --> DB : reads
SS --> DB : updates

' === Notes for architectural decisions ===
note right of EB
  Centralized EventBus (Singleton)
  Enables loose coupling per ADR 1
  Persists events for reliability
end note

note right of UM
  Centralized RBAC enforcement
  Authorization filter intercepts all requests
end note

note left of PM
  State machine pattern
  Optimistic concurrency control (version)
end note
@enduml